The paper deals with error-correcting codes, specifically Reed-Solomon codes, under the insdel metric. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also involves constructions of codes, which could fall under the data structures (cs.DS), distributed computing (cs.DC), and coding theory and cryptography (cs.CC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with synchronization errors in communication systems, which could fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
